  "text": "1. **Overflow reset reason string**: Defined in `source/common/http/utility.cc:1031` inside `Utility::resetReasonToString()`, which maps `Http::StreamResetReason::Overflow` \u2192 `\"overflow\"`. The enum itself is in `envoy/http/stream_reset_handler.h:33`.\n\n2. **Connection pool overflow triggers**: Both occur in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`:\n   - Line 282-287 (`newStream`): Checks `pendingRequests().canCreate()` \u2014 if the pending request circuit breaker is tripped (controlled by `max_pending_requests`), it fires `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`.\n   - Line 175-180 (`attachStreamToClient`): Checks `requests().canCreate()` \u2014 if the max requests circuit breaker is tripped (controlled by `max_requests`), it fires `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`.\n   The `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` is translated to `StreamResetReason::Overflow` in `source/common/router/upstream_request.cc:569-570`, then `router.cc:1415-1420` builds the full error message.\n\n3. **Circuit breaker proto**: `envoy/config/cluster/v3/circuit_breaker.proto` in data-plane-api defines `CircuitBreakers.Thresholds` with `max_connections` (field 2, line 59) and `max_pending_requests` (field 3, line 64), both defaulting to 1024.",
